reviews.review_text: Thanks GD! A wonderful sounding show, just lovely. ❤❤

Thank you! Really enjoying this show, so many great versions of great tunes! Such a treat that we can listen to these shows from over 50 years ago and in excellent audio quality. Next best thing to being there, but I was only 9 when they played this show and my parental units were definitely not going to be taking us there! :)

might as well before the new year, i was hoping (at least my intention went) that somehow i would limit the intake of Grateful Dead shows. i tried sticking with 1972 because you can't go wrong, close your eyes and throw the dart...whatever you hit, whichever show, it's probably gonna be good. if not amazing psychedelic music for any afternoon, sobriety damned. then i got thinking, maybe i try 77? it's what got me into the Dead, cornell was perfect, for the budding enthusiast. that scarlet/fire is mean! but i thought, again, if it's gonna be good, it might as well be perfect. so let's see what all the talk is about... ( 1976 ) the year after so much questioning, searching for answers in a field of daises...i tried 07/17/76 but came up short...seems they just missed something, but the 2nd set is good don't get me wrong. I'm just lookin for something, not sure what...but when I find it, I have a feeling, strong inspection, that i'll know right away.

Great Review from Nick! Reflects my philosophy regarding a random thought or a highlight of the show that forces a connection into the light! might have nothing to do with anything... but might seem relevant to ALL OF IT! And yeah, the show's good too!
